Langan Engineering, Environmental, Surveying and Landscape Architecture, D.P.C. Geo-Site Structural Engineer - 8+ Years Experience in New York , New York 
Work for an Industry Leader 
Outstanding Opportunities 
Challenging Projects 
Dynamic Work Environment 
Langan is an award-winning ENR Top 500 Design Firm that offers integrated engineering and environmental services for both public and private sector clients at sites located throughout the United States and abroad. Langan receives numerous recognitions for its technical expertise as well as its work environment, including Zweig Group’s Best Firms to Work For, Glassdoor’s Employees’ Choice Award – Best Places to Work, NJ Biz Best Places to Work and Business of the Year – 50 Fastest Growing Companies, Hartford Business Journal’s Best Places to Work in CT, and Pittsburgh Business Times - Best Places to Work in Western PA. Visit our website for more information about our awards and recognitions. 
Langan offers its employees opportunities that provide challenge and responsibility within an environment where they can grow and flourish! Join our team of industry leaders and make a difference on some of the most exciting and interesting projects in the field! 
Langan is seeking a Geo-Site Structural Engineer with 8+ years of experience to work in either our Philadelphia, PA; Parsippany, NJ; New York, NY; or Arlington, VA office. The successful candidate will have the ability to develop effective, attractive structural design solutions for unique situations in support of site-civil and landscape architectural design projects. You will also support the geotechnical and waterfront engineering groups throughout various Langan offices. This position offers significant opportunity for professional growth including but not limited to development and management of his or her own group, client interaction and development, and much more! 
Typical geo-structural engineering for site-civil engineering and landscape architecture projects include reinforced-concrete design of site structures such as retaining walls, stairs, ramps, pavements, rooftops and specialty site and landscape structures; loading calculations for fences and railings; footing and foundation design for site lighting, fences, bollard and site furnishings, stone and masonry-clad walls, decking and boardwalks; and design of other concrete, steel and timber construction. Typical geo-site structural analysis and design support for geotechnical and waterfront projects includes: support-of-excavation, underpinning, slope stabilization, utility support, ground-improvement, shallow and deep foundations, earth-retaining structures and grouting programs. Other tasks will include design and oversight of positive cutoff walls, dewatering systems, and waterfront features such as railings, paving materials, and site furnishings. 
Job Requirements: 
Master’s degree in Civil Engineering with a Structural focus from an ABET-accredited university; 
Minimum of 8 years of demonstrated geo-structural, architectural and/or geotechnical experience; 
Professional Engineer licensure; 
Intimately familiar with soil and rock mechanics, soil-structure interaction analysis and design, numerical analysis and LRFD methodology; 
Solid understanding of building codes that guide site-civil and landscape architecture design and construction, along with practical knowledge about traditional and innovative materials and finishes; 
Excellent interpersonal skills and ability to work collaboratively with co-workers, management and clients; 
Strong technical skills, analytical ability and attention to detail; 
Possess effective time-management skills and ability to balance multiple concurrent tasks, responsibilities, and commitments; 
Strong verbal and written communication skills; and, 
Ability to travel is required along with a valid driver’s license in good standing. 
Langan offers its employees opportunities that provide challenge and responsibility within an environment where they can grow and flourish! 
We offer competitive compensation packages; full-time employment company paid medical, dental, and vision coverage; life insurance, short- and long-term disability insurance; 401(k)/Roth with company match; extensive training; buddy and mentoring programs; employee referral and professional license bonuses; educational reimbursement; and much more! 
Equal Opportunity Employer
